uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.owl.reason

Class ORClassifier

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model.motor.IReasonerDefault
      • uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model.motor.IClassifier
        • uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.network.NClassifier
          • uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.owl.reason.ORClassifier
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IReasoner

    public class ORClassifier
extends NClassifier
    Provides OWL-classification-based versions of the reasoning mechanisms defined by IReasoner, based on classifications involving either class-expressions or networks of individuals.

    The instance-level frames that are passed into the classify(uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.network.NNode, uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model.motor.IClassifierOps) method, are converted into the intermediate network representation, which is what the abstract methods implemented by the derived classes will operate on.

    The classification process can be customised by adding one or more pre-processors to modify the networks that will be passed to the methods on the derived class (see NClassifier.addPreProcessor(uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.network.NProcessor)).

    After any required pre-processing the networks are then processed to ensure "ontology-compliance". This ensures that they will only contain entities for which equivalents exist in, or for which substitutions can be made from, the relevant ontology. Hence, any nodes whose associated concepts do not have equivalents in the ontology, will either be modified to reference appropriate ancestor-concepts (as determined by looking at the frames model), or else removed from the network. Also, any links whose associated properties do not have equivalents in the ontology will be removed from the network.
